"Abstract The Circuit Layouts Act 1989 (Cth) commenced in Australia on 1 October, 1990 and was subsequently amended by Part 3 of the Law and Justice Legislation Amendment Act 1990 (Cth) which came into effect on 21 December, 1990. The legislation has recently been the subject of interpretation in two important cases - Avel Pty Ltd & Ors. v Wells (Federal Court, New South Wales Division, 2 December 1991) and Nintendo Co Limited v Centronics Systems Pty Ltd & Ors. (Federal Court, Victorian Division, 9 December 1991). The purpose of this article is to consider the implications of these decisions, particularly on the question of how the legislation impacts upon parallel importation and reverse engineering of semiconductor technology."
